records.addlTxt:
Defendant Truman R Katula in court, in custody, with attorney Thomas J McClure.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
State files an amended information.
Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
Defendant's mother spoke.
  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9 MONTHS JAIL; if revoked, the first 60 days to be served as straight time and the balance with Huber, w/Standard Release Conditions (CREDIT - Held open); Consecutive to any sentence if revoked.

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No violent contact with any family member.
*Psychological evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.

COURT COSTS:  $243 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
